com.android.internal.telephony
Interface ITelephony

All Superinterfaces:
IInterface
All Known Implementing Classes:
ITelephony.Stub
public interface ITelephony
extends IInterface

Interface used to interact with the phone. Mostly this is used by the TelephonyManager class. A few places are still using this directly. Please clean them up if possible and use TelephonyManager insteadl.

dial

void dial(String number)
          throws RemoteException
Dial a number. This doesn't place the call. It displays the Dialer screen.

Parameters:
number - the number to be dialed. If null, this would display the Dialer screen with no number pre-filled.

showCallScreen

boolean showCallScreen()
                       throws RemoteException
If there is currently a call in progress, show the call screen. The DTMF dialpad may or may not be visible initially, depending on whether it was up when the user last exited the InCallScreen.

Returns:
true if the call screen was shown.
Throws:
RemoteException

showCallScreenWithDialpad

boolean showCallScreenWithDialpad(boolean showDialpad)
                                  throws RemoteException
Variation of showCallScreen() that also specifies whether the DTMF dialpad should be initially visible when the InCallScreen comes up.

Parameters:
showDialpad - if true, make the dialpad visible initially, otherwise hide the dialpad initially.
Returns:
true if the call screen was shown.
Throws:
